# ABSTRACT

House Hunt – Finding Your Perfect Rental Home is a web-based application  
developed to simplify the process of searching and renting apartments.  
The application helps users find rental homes efficiently based on  
location, price, and preferences.

The system eliminates traditional challenges such as broker dependency,  
lack of transparency, and time-consuming manual searches. Using modern  
web technologies like MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, and Node.js (MERN  
Stack), the platform offers a secure, scalable, and user-friendly  
solution.

This project aims to provide a centralized platform for property owners  
and tenants, ensuring smooth interaction and reliable information  
sharing.

---

# 1. INTRODUCTION

In today's fast-paced world, finding a suitable rental home is a  
challenging task. Traditional house-hunting methods are time-consuming,  
inefficient, and often involve intermediaries who increase costs.

House Hunt is designed to bridge the gap between tenants and property  
owners by providing a digital platform that allows users to search,  
view, and contact property owners directly.

The application offers features such as apartment listings, filtering,  
secure authentication, and responsive design to improve user experience  
and reliability.

---

# 2. OBJECTIVES OF THE PROJECT

- To provide an easy and efficient way to find rental homes  
- To eliminate dependency on brokers  
- To ensure transparency in property listings  
- To allow property owners to manage listings easily  
- To develop a scalable web application using MERN stack  

