# 4. IDEATION PHASE

The ideation phase focuses on identifying the real-world problem and  
developing a feasible solution using technology. The idea for the House  
Hunt project originated from the difficulties faced by people while  
searching for rental homes.

Traditional methods involve brokers, manual visits, and lack of  
accurate information. These challenges motivated the development of a  
digital platform that connects tenants and property owners directly.

## 4.1 Problem Statement

Finding a rental home is often time-consuming and inefficient due to  
the involvement of intermediaries, lack of transparency, and outdated  
information. Tenants struggle to find suitable homes that match their  
preferences, while property owners face difficulties in reaching  
potential tenants.

## 4.2 Proposed Solution

The proposed solution is a web-based application that provides a  
centralized platform for listing and searching rental properties. The  
system allows tenants to search homes based on location, price, and  
requirements, while owners can list and manage their properties easily.

The platform eliminates broker dependency and ensures direct  
communication between users and owners.

## 4.3 Empathy Map

The empathy map was used to understand user behavior, needs, and pain  
points. It helped in designing features that improve user satisfaction  
and usability.

