# 6. PROJECT DESIGN PHASE

The project design phase focuses on defining the overall system structure  
and workflow of the House Hunt application. This phase transforms the  
requirements into a structured design that guides development.

## 6.1 System Design

The system is designed as a web-based application following a modular  
architecture. It separates frontend, backend, and database layers to  
ensure scalability and maintainability.

The design enables smooth interaction between users, application logic,  
and data storage.

## 6.2 Proposed Solution Design

The proposed design allows tenants to browse rental properties and  
owners to manage listings through a centralized platform. Secure login  
and role-based access control are implemented for better security.

## 6.3 Solution Architecture

The House Hunt application follows a **three-tier architecture**:

### Presentation Layer
- Developed using React.js
- Handles user interface and user interactions
- Displays listings, forms, and dashboards

### Application Layer
- Developed using Node.js and Express.js
- Handles business logic and API requests
- Manages authentication and authorization

### Data Layer
- Uses MongoDB database
- Stores user details, property data, and login credentials
- Ensures efficient data retrieval and storage

The architecture ensures secure communication between all layers and  
supports future enhancements.

