# 8. PROJECT DEVELOPMENT PHASE

The project development phase focuses on the actual implementation of  
the House Hunt – Finding Your Perfect Rental Home application. The system  
was developed using the MERN Stack, following a modular and structured  
approach.

## 8.1 Frontend Development

The frontend of the application was developed using React.js to provide  
a responsive and interactive user interface. The UI components were  
designed to enhance user experience and ease of navigation.

Key features of frontend development include:
- Responsive design for multiple devices
- Component-based architecture
- Apartment listing and detail pages
- User login and registration forms
- Search and filter functionality
- Dashboard for users

React Router was used for navigation between different pages, and form  
validation was implemented to ensure correct user input.

## 8.2 Backend Development

The backend of the application was developed using Node.js and  
Express.js. It handles all business logic, API requests, and data  
processing.

Key backend functionalities include:
- RESTful API development
- User authentication using JWT
- Property listing management
- Secure request handling
- Integration with MongoDB database

The backend ensures smooth communication between the frontend and the  
database.

## 8.3 Database Development

MongoDB was used as the database for storing application data. The  
database stores information related to users, property listings, and  
authentication details.

Mongoose was used to define schemas and manage database operations,  
ensuring data consistency and integrity.

